===Noun===
'''marriage'''  (''plural:'' '''[[marriages]]''')
<!--Note: this definition is this long, to stave off the POV edit battles that were erupting.  If you wish to change this first one, you are probably wrong; please read up on some of the conversation from the talk page and discuss it on IRC first.-->
# A social, religious and/or legal [[union]] that usually forms the nucleus of a [[family]], in Western cultures generally between one man and one woman, i.e., [[husband]] and [[wife]] ([[monogamy]]); in most societies it may also consist of a [[union]] of a man and multiple women ([[polygyny]]), and in some societies may comprise unions between a woman and multiple men ([[polyandry]]), same-sex unions between two women or two men, or unions among multiple men and multiple women ([[w:group marriage|group marriage]]).
#: '''Examples'''
#* ''The king of Swaziland recently entered into '''marriage''' with his thirteenth wife.''
#* ''The Netherlands allows '''marriage''' between same-sex couples.''
#* ''Conservative Western Christians believe that '''marriage''' should be limited to the union of one man and one woman.''
# A wedding.
#* ''You are cordially invited to the '''marriage''' of John Smith and Jane Doe.''
# A close union.
# A joining of two parts.

